caption: The food is amazing!!!! Great service everything came out hot and delicious! Love love love the elote man tamales!! A must try!
The pozole was delicious!
5 stars +. Great service, delicious food, authentic atmosphere.

We decided to come eat here bc of the reviews & it was a great choice. The atmosphere, food, and drinks were great. The pozole verde had a nice spicy kick to it while the red was tasty but not spicy. We all ordered different meals and they were all great!
Five stars. Just go here. It’s incredible.
Had some great empanadas and drinks

Love Estrella Negra! Wonderful little place with a lot of style, (the decor is so vibrant and fun), friendly staff and GREAT food. The pozole is super tasty. I've had both the Rojo and Verde pozoles and both are legit, so good. And perfectly spicy. Everything else I've had is top notch, especially the burritos and tortas. HUGE portions, so order hungry. Highly recommend this place!

Staff is great and the food is AMAZING! My husband and I decided to try this place after reading the reviews. We ordered a few things recommended to us when we called and were overly impressed with how great everything tasted. We tried the wings, chicken enchiladas, soup, and the goat cheese quesadilla. I would recommend all of it again (especially the quesadilla) to anyone that asks.

Love Estrella Negra! Been a fan since the beginning and they keep getting better with age. The Pozole is amazing, but their Chilaquiles have ruined me for every other restaurant that I have tried them in. Try them! Worth it every time!!!
Goat cheese quesadilla was excellent! Service and recommendations also excellent!
The vegan pozole verde is WHERE IT’S AT!!! I’ve never really gotten to try pozole because I don’t eat meat, but my goodness it was fantastic — and they also sell it by the gallon 👀👀
Omg! So much flavor,so awesome service,and great atmosphere, great at keeping it safe at social distancing and mask wearing!
Unique upscale Mexican street food, creatively crafted cocktails, excellent service.
Food is fantastic, drinks are good!

The food and the service was stellar! Have passed by this place a million times and so glad we decided to stop on for a light dinner and drinks. The ambiance is very nice and even a bit romantic. We had the pozole rojo, chicken and poblano empanadas and the surf and turf burger. Everything was so delicious, every bite was full of flavor and incredibly satisfying. The caipirinhas were amazing too! I highly recommend this little place if you're looking for  meals and drinks worth the menu price as well as great service and ambiance. Can't wait to go back!
This place is awesome. Everything we got was delicious, and I love all their salsas. They have really interesting dishes - the goat cheese mango quesadilla with mango salsa was so good!

Small cozy place with authentic art work as table tops which you can purchase. The food is to die for! Loved how they made Mexican food with a twist. Try fried Avocados, pozole, Tacos with goat cheese instead of the regular shredded cheese.
I love Estrella Negra. The food is always great and the staff is always friendly and amazing!

I love the take on Mexican street food that this place consistently provides.  The flavors are deliciously combined and complimented nicely with their drinks.  My favorite is their brunch menu...yummy!  Tamarindo wings are a must have.  Service is great too.  One time I had an emergency and had to leave suddenly.  Told the waiter my dilemma and headed to the bathroom quickly, by the time I came back my food was packed and ready to go.  Much appreciated.

My favorite Mexican restaurant, hands down. Delivers in flavor, and true to Mexican cuisine. Great atmosphere & beautiful artwork by local artists hang inside. Highly recommend the vegan green pozole.
Tamarindo chicken wings are 🔥🔥🔥 and are a must try. Pozole and garza fries are also delicious here. I have recommended it to friends and family. Only thing is potions have gotten smaller.
Everything was good until I found a bone in my chicken taco
Delicious food, always. Loved the green tea horchata!
A nice bowl of posole with a bandera shot is sure to cure any ailment .  Great staff,  chill environment, and an awesome menu for everyone.
Love this place! I go here on the regular and the food is always fantastic, tons of delicious vegetarian options and friendly staff 😊
My husband and I both love this place. We don't come here often (prob 2-3 times a year), but when we do, we are never disappointed. With both drinks and food, we enjoy it every time.
Brunch here is great if you enjoy Mexican cuisine!

This space is amazing. The food is quite incredible and the pozole is legitimately one of the best I’ve had.  I’d suggest making reservations, being so delicious makes them very popular. To ensure your space on busy days this would be wise.  Make sure to come with friends so you can try more things on the menu.  The wings and fried avocado in the brunch menu 🔥
Really good food but sort of pricey. Cocktails are the bomb though
The food was heavenly! And the service was fantastic. I thoroughly recommend trying "La Bandera" if you're in the mood for a unique drinking experience.
Perfect dinner at a great price
Excellent food  nice flavored and excellent service bartender and waiters . Highly recommended

This place was amazing ,first off the ambience inside is dope ,it has a lot of culture and beautiful colorful hand painted painting from Mexican culture just beautiful, the food was excellent, I tried their award winning chicken wings ,which were fried with a special sauce with crumbled of goat cheese on top,  their steak tacos were very tender, i also enjoyed their mango guacamole which was really good and last i enjoyed a smokey mezcal, which was awesome ,i will be returning and bringing friends ,you gotta go ,you will love this small quaint spot  another Chicago Certified Stamped place for excellent food  P.S the food is so authentic the mom cooks the food it doesnt get any better than that ENJOY I KNOW I DID 🤗❤ S

Good, fresh Mexican at a reasonable price. The shrimp and mango enchiladas are unique and tasty. Also highly recommend the empanada sampler. The chicken pozole is spicy and satisfying, really some of the best in the city.
Best Mexican food anywhere in Chicago. Ask for mezcal and you’ll taste the best around.
AWESOMENESS!
Great food and drinks! Fried, chorizo burrito, and margarita were all great!

I have eaten here a handful of times. Gorgeous decor. The food is good but the portions always seem pretty small. Have also found the management to be a bit aloof and rude at times. I probably won't make a point of trying again, especially not after the disappointing portions I got last time, and the way I was treated when I complained.
Awesome food , awesome Service

Cool decor and very nice staff. However, the food was meh. I ordered the steak burrito with side of seasoned fries. It was THE saltiest and the most peppered steak ever. Not much of a seasoning or flavor at all. The size of the burrito was pretty small. The meat was tender, i give you that.  Latin food means comfort to me and this didnt cut it. Might go back to try the famous chicken enchiladas. 🤷🏻‍♀️

Estrella Negra is exceptional. I had the guacamole and chips to start with my traditional margarita. I ordered the award winning Chicken enchiladas and the award is merited.  The staff is friendly and the service is also exceptional. Highly recommended.

It is not your typical Mexican restaurant. It has more of a high end feel to it. The tamarindo wings were delicious, the ceviche was very fresh and limey! The spinach and cheese empanadas were also tasty! The michelada was too spicy for me, but I’m sure if you like spicy, you’ll love it! Good thing we live at a walkable distance because parking would be hard.

My favorite was the poblano tamal special and the sweet potatoe fries. Everything else was just ok (tamarind wings, chorizo tacos, empanada. The wait was about 30 minutes (lunch hour) for the food. Parking was a bit challenging to find. The space was fun.
Great food and drinks
Great food and service!
Delicious food and great service.

The food portions are small for the price.  Service is very slow.  We didn't realize gratuity was included on our bill and left a tip until we got home.  We called to let them know and were told that the manager would call to straighten it out but never did.  We will never visit or recommend this place to friends and family!
Awesome chicken tacos. Tasty a little smokey but that added to FAVOR TOWN! HIGHLY RECOMMENDED.

First of all the Pozole is probably one of the best dishes on that menu. It was delicious, not all watered down like other places. Also the tamarindo wings caught me by surprise. They were delicious as well. Out of the 6 things my wife and I ordered we loved all 6 of them. That snickers empanada had me at hello!
Waited for over an hour for our food, which was mediocre and like warm. Bean dip was good. Service wasnt the best. mango mojito was tasty.
Good food, good drinks, good music. You can ring my bell!

Oh bucktown, back in the chilapan days you used to own the mexican food scene. And now... the neighborhood has turned into an overpriced bougie approximation of mexican food. This place unfortunately is no different.  If you order a side of guac you get ... a teaspoon of guac. The entrees were small and unexceptional. The cookie tamale that everyone raved about was meh. I'm still hungry, search for good bucktown mexican food continues.

First time I heard of this place was at Ruido Fest and right from the first bite it tasted amazing. The empanadas are highly recommend, especially the goat cheese one. After festival found out their exactly location and went to try out the actual restaurant and it didn't disappointed. Everything tasted so amazing from their cocktail drinks to the dessert options. Highly recommend this place if you're in the Northside of Chicago and are looking for some amazing food.
Delicious!! Everything is bueno
Good Posole

Enjoyed his place. Started off with chips and guacamole. I thought it was bland. The salsa that came with the chips was very spicy and good, I really liked it. For dinner we got the steak tacos and veggie enchiladas. Both came with a side, I elected for the tortilla soup which had shrimp and chicken. I thought it had very good flavor. Wife got French fries which were good but standard. Enchiladas were very flavorful and tasty. Steak tacos came with almost a slaw on top and the steak was tender. I will go back. Each had a drink and the tab was $50 so even price was very reasonable
Great food and staff with nice atmosphere

The concha burger and the steak fries were simply amazing. The green grass horchata was possibly the best I have ever had. Two things though.... we had a big table. Everyone got their food late and apart. At one point someone waited 40 minutes. In general we waited a long time to get our food. Two of our order wings.. we never got. They only had one server.. she was super sweet.. but was literally serving the entire place. Overall this place was good.

Otoniel and the entire staff on hand at Estrella Negra were a delight to work with! They kindly helped us host a Sunday brunch event for about 20 people in July and were extremely accommodating to our guests!  In addition to their flexibility, the food was incredible... BONUS: the bloody marys were perfect and spicy! I can't recommend this place enough!  Special thanks to our fantastic server Fernando as well!

Brought my out of town friends here by random pick and could not have been happier!  The menu is a creative take on typical Mexican dishes and the vibe is eclectic and laid back.  We tried the spicy chicken pozole, mango salsa enchiladas, and the sweet potato "churros", amongst other things, and everyone was really impressed with their choices. I'll definitely be coming back!
Check Please and Chicago's Best have visited. Food is excellent. Creative menu, interesting art on the walls and really good music playing from Pandora our server claimed.
Incredible food with extremely well balanced flavors. Standouts are the pozole and empanadas and for sides highly recommend the bean dip! It's a small place and can get busy very fast.

Food was great.
I LOVED it sooooo much. Mexican food with a modern twist but oh so delicious  My mom loved the tamarind wings and I loved the elite tamal and the enchiladas with mango salsa. Bomb!

It's a great place. The food is excellent. The appetizers are so good you could it only from them. The service was slightly slow and our silverware and plates appeared dirty. Such a pitty because better service would make this a 10.

Lovely little Mexican joint in Bucktown.  I love the decorum as it made me feel like I was off of historic route 66 in New Mexico or Arizona. The food felt authentic to my home state of Arizona but with an original flare to them. The tamales were excellent and my Jalapeno margarita was nicely prepared and very tasty. The wait staff was friendly and attentive.
Estrella Negra has great food and pleasant attentive servers. One of my favorite mexican places in Chicago.
I loved the food! LOVED the appetizers more than they’re actual entres. But nontheless. It was soooooo good!!
mouthwatering pozole 🤤, 🔥 drinks!
Great tasting food. Wasnt a fan of the dessert selection but we were there for real food and drinks and it was all amazing. No one at our table left a speck on our plates

Wow this place is amazing! Out go-to’s are the carne asada fries, the empanada sampler, the tamarind chicken wings (award winning), some fun drinks and of course chips. There is almost always a wait but call ahead and they can pencil you in! Great service too but the food is next level!

Really adorable little spot that features art from local Hispanic artists in the area on the walls and delicious and invented Mexican cuisine on the plates! Love the vibrant energy of the space and the staff was very accommodating and warm. Ordered a simple quesadilla and a Nutella tamale for dessert and both were delicious and very filing.  I was told it's a late night kind of place so after a night of drinking had here for some authentic Mexican eats and more drinking!

What an incredible gift this restaurant is to the city of Chicago! Popped in on a Saturday afternoon,  with a group of six. We were greeted and served by Fernando. He was on top of everything. Oto, the owner also came out and greeted us. Between the group, we shared everything on the menu. Wings (apparently #2 in the city)  and pozole were my personal favorites, but honestly,  I would order anything and be ecstatic about it. Music was great and the local artwork around the place (all artwork, including table tops, were for sale) were the icing on the cake. I will probably make another trip to Chicago, just so I can go to Estrella Negra again. Thanks guys!

This is an excellent spot! Went with friends for brunch and everything we ordered off the menu was great! The mexi-mosas were a fun kick and stronger than expected. The guacamole was really good and I don't like guacamole! The pozole is also great!
The food is Amazing!!! mexican fusion at its finest. Great spot . Highly recommended.
Good food and drinks
Can I just say: Carne. Asada. Fries?! SO GOOD!
Always a great time
Came for their first place wings and everything was good, the servers were nice too . Will be going back. Nicely decorated cozy spot
The enchiladas could be more saucy but always good food. This is the only pozole that comes close to my moms. 2 thumbs up!

I visited this family owned Mexican restaurant with friends and they did not disappoint! Great music, delicious cocktails, attentive service, tons of local art (all for sale by the way), and the best empanadas! Actually the whole menu is amazing but my top favorites were the spinach and artichoke empanadas, the pozole (crazy good), and the enchiladas. Vegetarian and vegan options available too. I'll definitely be going back!

I really wanted to love this place based off my first visit a month ago. Yesterday, early evening my sister, my brother-in-law and I went to estrella negra for dinner. I came across an Instagram post from the restaurant that  advertised taco Tuesday(margarita and tacos for six dollars- no details on quantity). What a steal!! I know! WRONG!!! we get there and the waitress takes our order. I wanted to be sure about the  promo so I asked her if the pricing is correct?  She had no idea what I was talking about so I pulled up the post for her. After she reviewed it she stepped away to call her manager to confirm the promo as she was unaware. The manger didn't answer her call so she agreed to honor the promo at six dollars. The meal than would consist of three tacos and a margarita per person. Great! We placed our order for the 2nd time with a total of nine tacos and three margaritas. The waitress came back to our table 20 mins after we placed our order and tells us the manger had called back and modified the prices. Ha! So now the tacos would be three dollars a piece and margaritas at six dollars a piece. She preceded to ask us if we wanted to modify the quantity of tacos. So after all that of course we did! We ordered six tacos instead all with NO ONION! 30 mins later (now at 50 mins) we received our tacos and they all had onion. Since I refused to send my food back I decided to take the onion out myself. I was waiting for the waitress to check on our table and she didn't show her face. My brother-in-law asked her for the check and still didn't receive it after 15 mins of waiting. He took it upon himself to walk up to the bar area and ask for it instead. I'm beyond disappointed with the entire dining experience. Owners if your reading this.. do the consumers a favor and stop posting false promos! It hurts your business more than you think.
The pozole tastes like home. I really like this place. Great service too. Decent prices.

My waitress seemed like she didn't want to take our order or even work there . My bf and I were like the only ones there and we didn't get our appetizer until like 30 mins later and when we got our tacos they were already cold and she didn’t even asked us if we needed anything else afterwards.

My husband and I both got food poisoning after eating here. The tamales tasted delicious, but not worth the food poisoning. Also, we were not a fan of the salsas that were served at a hot temperature.

This place had average food, but a cool atmosphere and great service (we were the only people there on a friday night). The food had no real identity. It wasnt authentic Mexican, it wasnt tex mex, it wasnt healthy or trendy. I had a burrito with a dried out, room temperature spinach wrap, the kind I get at a school cafeteria. Then there unshredded romaine lettuce! When I want a burrito, I dont want a chunk of dry spinach wrap and romaine lettuce! The place has good intentions, but poor execution. Food was average and a bit overpriced. Drinks were well balance and delicious though.
Everything is excellent, visit again and again.

Delicious food, and had some great music playing (deadmau5,  bassnectar, Daft Punk, Benny Bennassi). My only wish was more guacamole.

Cool place, the set up artistic. Menu dish names are based of La Loteria, that's pretty cool. Arrived with out reservation, had a 15 min wait. Others 20 / min wait time. So call in advance. The food was ok. The beer was good. The service was better. I recommend to check out the art installations.
Great latin food and a wonderful atmosphere

Amazing food!! Would definitely recommend this place to everyone. So much flavor in all the food and drinks. My go to are the enchiladas but you really can't go wrong with anything else either. The staff has been so kind everytime I have been in!

My new favorite place. Our server was unpleasant,  but the food was AMAZING!!!!

Understand that the food is not terrible , but nothing about this restaurant is Mexican or redeemable. 16 dollar ceviche that is simply shrimp in a martini glass is not ceviche. This place was fantastic, great selection of vegetarian and vegan options. I particularly enjoyed the mushroom pozole, it was delicious I would definitely recommend it!
Food is original and amazing. Not a bad dish on the menu and owned by a born and bread chicagoan. Love the vibe and the deliciousness.
Very good food and drinks, but still unreasonably overpriced for what it is.

This small spot packs a lot in. Great art and feel to the room. Well taste & well balanced house margaritas. Food is fresh and delicious. Had tamale trio app, El Musico chicken sandwich, shrimp tostadas, & enchiladas. Entrees come with a bowl of posolé to start, so good!

This is the third time I have visited la estrella negra and it never disappoints.  The modern twist on my favorite dishes always amazes me. Try the Pozole, its my favorite.

We came here sat night, saw that it said mexican resturant a decided to give it a shot. I had a hard time figuring out what i wanted to eat because im a very picky eater. This place is def not a spot to just go get some tacos or a burrito. Its like one of those modern mexican eats. Most of the stuff that comes on the tacos i have never heard of. Most of it sounded like healthy like for example they had green-tea horcata, avacado shake, sweet potato churros, black bean dip and the items on the menu that was like that i just cant remember it all. I just got 3 curizo tacos and my fiance got steak tacos. It was still good i just would only get that everytime i would come here. I can see alot of people liking this place i just aint healthy enough for it. Which is my fault. I would still recommend this place for someone like that. I loved all the artwork too.
I fell in love with their chilaquiles and tamarind wings definitely a must!

Great service and honestly those steak fries was worth the trip.  The pozole was the perfect amount of spicy and a must try. I would skip the green tea horchata, I wasn't impressed but I wouldn't knock points for it.  Will be going back because I want to try the drinks.

This is now my boyfriend and I spot! One day we stumbled across the gem and we've been going back ever since. Everything on this menu is delicious and the place is very clean and never over packed. We never have a problem with service and we plan to continue visiting. The loaded fries are to die for!
Really good seasonal guac. Friendly service and a quirky, fun setting. We had the tamales and steak tacos. They were delicious. I'd definitely go back if I'm in the area again.

I've had a few things here over the years. I hope she never sees this, and if she does may she forgive me, but the chicken pozole is amazing, better than even hers.  The el valiente sandwich is very tasty. I love the mango salsa enchiladas, and the tacos (chicken and beef) have always been my go-to. They have fantastic Classic Margaritas as well.

Amazing food and location. I love the art and music.

Ive been checking on Estrella Negra for a little while on IG trying to find time to check them out. Ive seen plenty of entertaining images that caught my attention , mainly the Tamarindo Chicken wings, which are Great. They are Sweet but pack some low key heat that hits u after the bones have been dropped on your plate. I was surprised how tasty the Goat Cheese Empanadas are, goat cheese and salsa work well together. Make sure you eat your empanadas right away while they are fresh, they lose a little love once the crunchy crust is softened by the cream and salsa. Loved the fries they have a light crust on them as well. Store front/near store front parking is not much of a struggle on the weekend since the "no parking" restrictions are mon-fri. Nice selection of mexican and local beers, comfortable seating & staff. I personaly need to go back to try the elote man tamales. Enjoy.

One of my favorite restaurants in Chicago! Amazing service, beautiful presentation, great drinks, delicious food, beautiful art, I can keep going. Definitely put Estrella Negra on your Restaurants To Try list! 10/10 would go again!

co-workers and I met here for brunch. The food, atmosphere, and staff were fantastic. Try the carne asada fries and breakfast nachos.

I don't know why I waited so long to do this, but here we go.  Im not 100% sure if this is correct but I'm going to brag that I might have been THE first customer Estrella Negra had, also, I think I've had every single dish on the Menu thus far. The story begins like this: I drove by several times before the grand opening, getting out of work, coming down 90/94 exit, I was just waiting for this "Tattoo Parlor" to open so I can get Inked up! I even looked it up online to see what the schedule was... OOOOW surprise when the day came and me and my girlfriend headed to the place, to find that this magical spot was to not be a Tattoo parlor but now one of my All Time favorite eateries. I've celebrated my birthday here, friendsgivings, I even rented the place for my cousins baby shower once! Why? you may ask. Because I love the concept and the food is unique, traditional Mexican but with a Unique twist, healthy, some may say, and overall great tasty food!  The rest is History......  To all out here, do visit this fantastic place, good for date nights, friend gatherings and mingling bashes. Its a Family Owned and Operated, Local, which I highly support, People friendly restaurant with phenomenal food.
Absolutely delicious pozole and tacos.  I was not a fan of the tamales, too greasy and gooey.  The vegetarian pozole was also fabulous. We plan on being regulars.

Delicious food. Cool atmosphere. I've driven past here a million times. Finally stopped in for lunch. The Pozole is unbelievable. Took my friends there for brunch and they were blown away by food and service. Highly recommended.

I can honestly say that the food here is delicious. The tamales and the posole are on point, although i do wish that they would bring oregano and spices to customize your posole a little more and some tortillas. But it is super good anyway. The breakfast items are great too. The art work on the walls was amazing and the artist that painted the table in the booth i sat at is extremely talented. His initials are A.M. the bloody marias are delish and the other drinks are awesome too. If you like wine, its byob, and if youre a coffee person, they are serving dark matter coffee. Yummy. The deserts are also pretty great. Btw.. Try the tamarindo wings. You will never get over them. :)
(Translated by Google) SALTY OF TACOS.  (Original) SALTY AF TACOS.

Cool place we found on Google because we needed to do some shopping near by. It was about 6:30 on a Friday night and we walked in. There were reservation signs on every table and the rest were filled with people. We wanted a quick bite and we got seated (the reservations were for 7:30). Great margaritas, the steak tacos are delicious and the poblano enchiladas solid with a little Gita cheese twist. The spicy salsa is very spicy! We’ll be back. Friendly. Cosy. Even surprising given the location. And if it’s the weekend we’ll make a reservation!
This is a great lunch spot. The food is delicious and they have a lot of options. Each meal comes with an appetizer too. Good portion sizes and great food!
Keeps getting better each visit.
Amazing food and a really relaxed atmosphere
Tasty take on Mexican food. Cool atmosphere
Some of the best Mexican food with very reasonable prices. This restaurant deserves a Michelin star.
Chocolate tamales weren’t good! They were not fully cooked. Nachos were nasty.... and the tables & chairs were dirty.

I was a bit skeptical at first because it wasnt a "traditional" Mexican restaurant but I was pleasantly surprised. Order the steak nacho fries, chicken tacos that had delicious bacon inside of it, and a chicken quesadilla that had a mild mango flavor to it. Will go back again.

Awesome place. Decor is themed to the Mexican game...loteria. food options are typical yet have a odd twist to them. Staff is nice and friendly. I think that the only down side to this place is location... really busy area so no parking... at all
Wonderful little gem of a restaurant. The empanadas are particularly awesome as are all their Posole's! Everything is a win on this menu. Portions are generous. Drinks are refreshing. Go here!!
This is one of my favorite spots in the city! The food is affordable and plentiful -- and it's BYOB! It's no frills and looks a little best up in there but it sure is good!!
Love the food. Reasonable prices.
Best place ever
Tasty Mexican food in funky, Day of the Dead decor.  Very nice wait staff.  Loved the tamales.
Love this place. Great eats, music, and friendly staff. Definitely recommend!!!

The portions are a good size. I'm in love with their organic green tea orchata, I buy it every time I'm here. Their empanadas are definitely solid and full of goat cheese. I've been coming here for the past 6 years.

This is where I go when my mother is in town.  My mom, like many Latino mothers as I've come to note, always has SOMETHING to say about the food that is served and not cooked by her.  It's overcooked, the rice is from last night, 'no tiene chiste' she could easily make the dish herself I should pay her to cook it instead. But when we come to Estrella the table is dead silent. Even though the ingredients and flavors are not entirely traditional, the dishes themselves are. It's a good compromise/in-between and it's so so good. My mom approves and doesn't try to beat it.  This is also where I go for a good margarita..EYYY
Great food. Great service. Perfect place for brunch or dinner.
Good wings. Didn't enjoy any of the drinks
Super delicious drinks, go during happy hour!
I love this places,  good food,  good drinks and excellent service
The jalapeno margarita is burning my lips off, but it's in a good way. Will definitely be back.
Good costumer service. A little different of what I use to know as Mexican food to say it like that. Great place!
Delicious brunch must try the chicken pozole with your entree
Excelente food, just the way it's supposed to be made with a little extra on top. Don't need to hope for my mom to make food anymore.
Sweet potato churro fries are amazing.

Love the feeling I get being in here, like I'm family. Food is so good and fresh, delicious drinks, cool art on the walls. I've yet to check out any of their special events or theme nights, but I look forward to doing so in the future
Great Tamales. And they serve Dark Matter coffe and espresso

We were able to seat us right away on a Sunday, they have a good selection of alcoholic beverages.  We had a side of sweet potato fries that was really good. They do offer vegetarian and vegan options to choose from. The offer their own version of Mexican food, the waiter was cordial and the service was fast. The Poblano enchiladas and Chorizo Quesadilla were OK.  Might come back again to try other dishes.
This is Not a BYOB
Food and drinks are good slow service
Very good food, and a nice atmosphere to have a good time.
Great food and drinks. A step up from a typical taco/burrito joint.

A very energetic and fun atmosphere. Food was great, but portions were a bit smaller than expected compared to typical Mexican restaurants in Chicago, so make sure to order an appetizer if you're really hungry.
Awesome food and service

My friend and I grabbed a bite to eat as we passed through town and we were happy with the meal. Service was cheerful, attentive, and provided well-founded recommendations on the menu. The decor and was my favorite part of the visit and the michelada and tacos, although different than what I expected, were good.

Decent food, not great. We ordered two orders of chips and salsa and still did not have enough chips, so we asked for more. They charged us. That's the theme of this place. $11 quesadilla... but $19 with shrimp. Go elsewhere. L'Patron, wherever.

The coffee is great, and sop is the food.  We love the decor, being a festive dia de los muertos/ sugar skull vibe. I am from San Diego, so I grew up on Mexican food. This is not authentic like my buddy's mom's home cooking, or even like a taco shop, but extremely delicious.  The have a lot of vegetarian options that help you forget you aren't eating meat if you want a healthy meal.
The food is amazing
Loved the brunch, and the steak fries were super delicious. Loved the chocolate chip tamale dessert too. Coming back ASAP 👌🏼
Fabulous flavors!
Awesome atmosphere, friendly service, great food

This place is awesome! From the food to the decor, everything about this place is just great! I had a family dinner there on Saturday and Oto was so great helping prepare for it. Once we were there, Fernando and the rest of the staff took such great care of us.  They were so professional and attentive. And the food was absolutely delicious! I definitely recommend this place!
Great food and great service I took my family there it was our first time going but not the last
Great food! Love the pozole! You also must try the chocolate chip tamal
Excellent Mexican Restaurant. They now have a liquor license and serve some great drinks.

I've walked by this place many times and missed it - but once I finally went it, I was so glad I did. Really love the guac here as well as the decor. I've never seen it too busy, but I've only gone on weeknights.

A total unassuming gem, with excellent and innovative Mexican-fusion eats.  We get different entrees each time, and are always impressed.  Their soup--a homemade corn-based chile of sorts--is enough to bring us back time and time again.  Beautiful, and sometimes a little freaky, artwork all over the walls, and on the tables themselves.  A cool place for sure!  BYOB!
great
Tacos are great!
Decent prices and good food.
The best place in chicago.

I made the mistake of being hungry and ordered an appetizer, assuming that it would come before the meal.  Each entree comes with a side, which isn't actually a side, but what comes before the rest of the food...but I wanted my side with my meal, and my appetizer before....silly me for not understanding.
Happy hour is the best but the mango salsa enchiladas were uh-MAZING! Great fast service, colorful decor, cool ambiance, delicious food and decent prices.
Chicken tacos and tamarind margarita.  Success!
Awesome place. Love the meat and mango enchiladas.  Great drinks and reasonable prices.
They are not BYOB anymore apparently. Decent food tho.
some of the tastiest mexican food in the area.
Get the Pozole soup as your side, its spicy and delicious!
One of my favorite hidden gems in Chicago. The food is delicious and the atmosphere is amazing.

Food tasted off, couldn't really put my finger on it. Guac and chips were average but shrimp enchiladas just didn't taste right. Margs were served in top heavy glasses that made it easy to spill. Decent beer list with some good local breweries like Revolution, etc.
Great originality. Date spot with classy hipness.
Steak torts was seriously amazing.   Margarita was delicious.  Try this place!
Amazing food and drinks! The new bar is amazing!
Bartender was super, very accommodating, I have special needs... Very important. Very original atmosphere and personality. Thanks!

I stopped in before a drive back to Columbus, Ohio for some takeout. These were the best tacos I've had for as long as I can remember. The steak was tender and flavorful...the salsa Verde was warm and delicious. the bean dip to die for...my only suggestion would be to add rice to the menu, my kids would have liked that and they expect it from any Mexican restaurant. they also put a new twist on an old fav....green tea horchata. I loved it, the kids didnt. I will be back on my next trip to chi town.

Terrible service. Food was actually decent but not good enough to make up for how unapologetically incompetent the service was, or for its relatively high price.  After being seated, we waited for like 15 minutes before anyone else even acknowledged we were there. No water, no silverware, no nothing. Service after that continued to be slow. It was busy but the staff didn't seem to have any sense of urgency or any idea that we had been waiting for so long. Really, a simple "Sorry about the wait" would have gone a long way.  Then I received steak enchiladas instead of the chicken I had ordered. To be fair, I didn't remember that I'd ordered chicken until I'd half-finished the food, and the enchiladas were good anyway. But still, they got the order wrong.  And, we still didn't have napkins or utensils by the time our entrees were served. And it was very difficult to get anyone's attention to ask for some.  And the crowd was obnoxious. But I guess that's not really the restaurant's fault.  Definitely never eating here again. I would think about maybe takeout, but the thing is there are so many better, cheaper options around this part of town, why bother?

Estrella Negra has been around for a while and for good reason.  It's good.  The food is Latin fusion.  I've enjoyed pretty much everything I've ever had here.  My favorites have been the empanadas and the tamales.  Historically this has been a BYOB spot but my last visit I saw signage stating that this was changing.  I hope that this isn't a trend across my short list of BYOB favorites.  Tip: Be sure to save room for dessert.

Go to Logan Arcade for a few hours then cross the street for some of the best Mexican food you'll ever have. Great service, great atmosphere.  Try the nachos with corn, the cinnamon and honey sweet potato fries, and the Dark Matter coffee. 👍
A truly fresh new experience, plus friendly service.

Great BYOB place with fun decor. The elote tamales are amazing, along with the goat cheese quesadillas and guacamole. Service can be a little slow from time to time, but overall a great place for tasty mexican.

BYOB!! No corkage fee! I went with a few friends and we ordered the ceviche, empanadas, and enchiladas, all of which were amazing! The food was all amazingly fresh and wonderfully executed. I would have to say the ceviche is my favorite so definitely try it out! They have a variety of sides to choose from such as fresh cut fries, sweet potato fries, and many others.
Cozy BYOB with great service. Try the La Escalera Mango Salsa Chicken Enchiladas - delicious!

We decided to stop by and try this place out for lunch. There are some great Dia Del Los Muertos paintings on the walls. The entire place looks like a cafe you'd find in Spain, or in the town of Ft. Kochi in India. Bold art, aggressive colors, interesting place. Coffee from Dark Matter. The food was decent – definitely go for brunch and try the breakfast burrito with chorizo, it's delicious.

Love this place!!! One of my favorite spots to eat in Chicago. Staff is super friendly and the vibe is relaxed. The steak tacos are delicious and the red salsa is spicy as hell but awesome. Oh yea and the artwork is decorating the interior is pretty sweet too. Highly recommend you try it out.
The food is amazing, great atmosphere
Enjoyed the atmosphere and the margarita mix but I think maybe ordered the wrong things... Nachos were ok, torta was not great, and enchiladas were sent back.
The food is so good!  The service could be better... but nonetheless I still recommend it highly (and am giving it five stars)!

Great place for comfort (at least to me) Mexican food. I was happy with the multiple vegetarian options. The tamales i had were the perfect portion size; I was able to eat the whole thing being satiated and not stuffed. The mango cheesecake (apparently from a bakery in Evanston) my wife and i shared was the perfect end to the meal.  The decor is interesting (Dia de los Muertos theme), and the music was cool without being loud. The staff was really friendly and helpful. We should go more often than we have!
Best enchiladas ever.  Staff is super friendly.  And the enchiladas are the best enchiladas ever.
Excellent food. Really cool enviroment and really nice staff. Take advantage of the 1/2 off vegetarian entrees on Tuesdays.

Very friendly staff! LOVED the food. Our absolute favorite were the empanada sampler, the sweet potato fries and, especially, the mango goat cheese quesadilla!! Totally recommend this place! Will def. be back very soon!

I went to Estrella Negra last night, and their food was beyond any other "Mexican food" that I have ever had.  Their menu selection and dishes combine different kinds and styles of food in a way that you would never think. Their style is best described as "gourmet Mexican."  All of their chips are handmade and made-to-order.  Fantastic service and even better food.
wonderful food fun decor and music  a hip mexican resturant prepares its food ith care
I really like the food, but one thing my friends and I have noticed is the prices on things have gone up way to much from when they first opened up. I don't think I will be back as often as I use to
i luv estrella negra i can even discribe how good their food taste. also all the people that work there are so nice and sweet and their food taste sooo fresh.i can not ask for more!!!!

Probably our favorite Mexican food in Chicago.  We appreciate all of the good vegetarian options.  The ingredients are fresh and the food is freshly prepared.  The dining area is informal, which suits our tastes.
Excellent food and an excellent value.
Great decor and the staff is VERY helpful will def visit every time I'm in Chicago
